original: Häge, Tord Arnold Natanael, läroverksadjunkt, Karlshamn, f. 27/7/06 i Öja, Malmöh. 1. — Stud:ex. 24, fil. mag. 29 o. teol. kand. 33, allt i Lund, provår v. norra latin i Sthlm 37-38. Vik. adj. i Karlskrona 30, e. o. ämneslär. v. Norrköp. komm. mellansk. 3)3-37, e. adj. i Sölvesborg 36-39, adj. i Västervik 39, adj. i kristend :kunsk. o. hist. m. ’S’am’h:lära v. Karlshamns samrealsk. sed. 46.
translated: Häge, Tord Arnold Natanael, high school teacher, Karlshamn, b. July 27, 1906 in Öja, Malmöh. Attended Lund University, graduated with a bachelor's degree in 1929, and earned a candidate degree in theology in 1933. Completed a probationary year at Norra Latin in Stockholm from 1937 to 1938. He had temporary positions as a teacher in Karlskrona in 1930, as a substitute subject teacher in Norrköping in 1933-1937, as a regular teacher in Sölvesborg from 1936 to 1939 and in Västervik in 1939. He became a regular teacher in Christian knowledge, history, and Sami theology at Karlshamn's junior high school from 1946 onwards. He married in the year 19xx.
